content: Use this almost daily! Real life saver when working patrol and time is short. Being able to save list of "favorites" for frequent violations is great for people that can't remember exact verbiage of these terribly written KRS violations.
replyContent:
My favorite part about the official KRS violations text is that they're all uppercase so I feel like the listings are yelling at me as I scroll through!

Thanks for the review!

content: Great app! Will you be updating with the new Kentucky Implied Consent that takes effect July 1, 2020?
replyContent: Implied Concent update will be available just before July 1st so the app doesn't have to display both.  Thanks for the review!

content: This is a great app! Very easy to use with no issues.
Fantastic app and a must have for anyone in the field. Use it nightly!
This app is well designed, easy to use, and a great resource for quick access to Kentucky revised statutes.
replyContent: Thanks for the review, I really appreciate it!

content: Good
Awesome app

Favorite keep disappearing. I've contacted owner tried all recommend fixes 
it's a shame it would be a great app except for that
replyContent:
I was unaware that someone wasn't able to resolved this issue that contacted me. Please reach out to me so I can resolve this as soon as possible.  You can reach me at my personal cell 270-977-7165 or email me at wmop3d@gmail.com.  

I'm sorry that this was ever an issue to begin with!  It was completely my fault.

content:
Pretty decent app. It use to link to the LRC site which was nicer because I 
knew it was up to date. Not as good as Ky Uors on the iPhone but it still 
helps save a ton of time on citations, discussions and with training new 
guys.
replyContent: Thanks for the review!  The issue with the LRC link was that when they updated a chapter, they kept the outdated link the same so you would still see the outdated listing until the link was updated within the app. I'll be adding ways to keep the app updated on its own if all goes as planned. It's currently working on that code now.

content: Great app but my favorites erase daily... Any fix?
replyContent:
There was a bug in the last release that I have corrected.  If you are still having the favorites issue, you will probably need to clear the apps cached data to resolve it.  Shoot me an email at wmop3d@gmail.com if you need help doing this.  I try to respond within minutes!

Sorry for the trouble!

content: Great resource for KY LEOs.  Developer responsive to issues.  Keep it up!
Just switched to android from IOS and I'm really glad to see this app. It comes in handy.
Great App For Ky Law

After being a police officer for over 10 years, this is hands down my new favorite app. The design of the app. is perfect for law enforcement use. Not only having the search tool to quickly and accurately find the charge you are looking for but, it also tells you if the charge is a violation, misdemeanor or felony and the elements of the charge. If the charge is arrestable or or just a citation.  Then to add the implied consent warning and thr miranada warning to it. Absolutely awesome app. Thank you
Helps out so much when on the field. Apps perfect! Thank you so much for efforts in making the app.
Peace officer
Great!!!!!
Love it
KRS. Very helpful
Well designed and easy to use.  Well done, man!
Outstanding.  Finally a usable resource for android that is updated as the Legislature makes changes to KRS
Still some bugs to fix but a very useful app overall!
Such a lifesaver! Keep up the good work!
Thankful I don't have to hunt down an iPhone user to get charges and violation codes everytime I need them. Thank you, best app ever.....work related.
Very glad this is here and it is very helpful!  Thanks!

I'm glad to see this is finally available. Very clean interface and quick searching. If you select a charge, it will take you to an online page providing the statutes criteria. Well done and liking forward to future updates.
Thank you! Being in an investigative unit, I don't always carry a code book with me so now I have it at my fingertips!! Yay!!
Finally! Thank you!
I'm glad you took the time to make this happen,IOS has had a similar app for some time and I have been waiting to be able to look these up on my Android.
replyContent: Thanks for the review!  If you want any features or changes to the app,  let me know and I'll make it happen.  I'm just a few weeks away from having the favorites section working properly for a release.

content: Great app.  It be awesome to see the KRS within the app itself.  About my only complaint.  Glad to finally see it on android!
replyContent: Thanks for the review!  I have made contact with the state to determine what steps I need to take so that I can legally make the KRS available offline.  Still waiting on a reply but I assure you that as soon as I can, the app will completely work with no service.

content: It's finally here and works great!
replyContent: Thanks for the review!  If you want any new features or find an issue with something, let me know and I'll take care of it!

content: So glad this is finally available on android! Love the simplistic design and ease of use.
It has a very simple interface. It's quick and responsive. It does exactly what it advertises.
